{"timestamp": "2025-12-07 00:02:39.947191", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nScope and intent\n- Topology: 2-tier pod (two leaves and two spines) with one super-spine. EBGP everywhere. Each leaf has a /24 host subnet: leaf_router_0_0 -> 10.0.0.0/24, leaf_router_0_1 -> 10.0.1.0/24.\n- Hosts under test: pc_0_0 (should be in 10.0.0.0/24) and pc_0_1 (should be in 10.0.1.0/24).\n\n1) High-level assessment\n- Control plane (BGP) appears healthy across leaves, spines, and super-spine. All EBGP sessions are Established with expected peer counts and nonzero prefixes received/advertised.\n- Data plane reachability across the fabric is generally good; multiple host-to-host pings succeed with low RTTs.\n- A localized end-host anomaly exists: pc_0_0 cannot perform reachability tests; this correlates with a misconfiguration on pc_0_0.\n\n2) Reachability observations\n- Automated reachability tests:\n  - pc_0_1 → various PCs: status ok with 0% loss, ~1–4 ms average RTT.\n  - pc_0_0 → various PCs: status unknown (no transmitted/received counts reported), indicating it is not successfully sending/receiving probe traffic.\n- Interface counters:\n  - pc_0_0 (eth0) shows TX 3, RX 0 packets; leaf_router_0_0’s host-facing interface (eth8, 10.0.0.1/24) shows RX 3 packets. This pattern is consistent with ARP broadcast from the host but no successful L3 traffic.\n\n3) Control plane status (evidence)\n- leaf_router_0_0 (AS 65200): BGP summary shows 8 peers all Established, PfxRcd ~31, PfxSnt ~32.\n- leaf_router_0_1 (AS 65201): Same as above, all Established.\n- spine_router_0_0 (AS 65100) and spine_router_0_1 (AS 65101): Established sessions with super-spine and all leaves; receiving prefixes as expected.\n- super_spine_router_0 (AS 65000): Established sessions with all spines; PfxRcd per peer is consistent.\n\n4) Device configurations and routing (evidence)\n- leaf_router_0_0 host subnet: eth8 = 10.0.0.1/24 (correct for pc_0_0).\n- leaf_router_0_1 host subnet: eth8 = 10.0.1.1/24 (correct for pc_0_1).\n- pc_0_1:\n  - IP 10.0.1.2/24, default gateway 10.0.1.1 (matches its attached leaf).\n- pc_0_0 (anomalous):\n  - IP 10.0.1.2/24, default gateway 10.0.1.1.\n  - This duplicates pc_0_1’s IP and places pc_0_0 in the wrong subnet/gateway for its physical attachment. It should be in the 10.0.0.0/24 network with gateway 10.0.0.1.\n\n5) Anomalies identified\n- Duplicate IP address: Both pc_0_0 and pc_0_1 are configured with 10.0.1.2/24.\n- Subnet/gateway mismatch on pc_0_0:\n  - pc_0_0 is physically connected to leaf_router_0_0 whose host-facing subnet is 10.0.0.0/24 (gateway 10.0.0.1).\n  - pc_0_0’s configuration points to 10.0.1.1 as default gateway, which is not on the L2 segment behind leaf_router_0_0 and hence not ARP-resolvable. This explains pc_0_0’s inability to send/receive routed traffic.\n\n6) Fault localization\n- Faulty device: pc_0_0.\n- Neighboring devices (leaf_router_0_0, leaf_router_0_1, spines, super-spine) show normal control plane and appropriate routing entries; no evidence of misbehavior in the fabric.\n\n7) Root cause\n- Misconfiguration on pc_0_0: incorrect IP addressing and default gateway assignment (10.0.1.2/24 via 10.0.1.1) instead of an address in 10.0.0.0/24 with default gateway 10.0.0.1. This also causes an IP address duplication with pc_0_1.\n\n8) Impact\n- pc_0_0 cannot reach other subnets or services through the fabric (ping tests from pc_0_0 fail/unknown).\n- The broader fabric remains stable and functional; only pc_0_0 is affected due to its local L3 misconfiguration.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 21807, "output_tokens": 3513, "total_tokens": 25320, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 0}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 2432}}}
